From: Kamil Lulko <limakzagan@gmail.com>
Subject: msi: make StartServices best-effort (services cannot run on Android)

Windows services generally cannot start on wine/Android (no real SCM / kernel
driver support). The iLok "License Support" installer registers and starts
PaceLicenseDServices; StartServiceW fails, ITERATE_StartService returns
ERROR_FUNCTION_FAILED, ACTION_StartServices returns 1627 and the install rolls
back at InstallFinalize — even though every file was already installed and the
iLok License Manager works without its background daemon.

Treat any service start/open failure in ITERATE_StartService as best-effort
success so the install completes instead of rolling back.

diff --git a/dlls/msi/action.c b/dlls/msi/action.c
index f750b875d6b..a6a51cafd97 100644
--- a/dlls/msi/action.c
+++ b/dlls/msi/action.c
@@ -6013,6 +6013,17 @@ static UINT ITERATE_StartService(MSIRECORD *rec, LPVOID param)
     }
 
 done:
+    /* vstpoc: on wine/Android, Windows services (e.g. PACE's PaceLicenseDServices)
+     * generally cannot start — but a failed StartServices must NOT roll back the
+     * whole install (the iLok License Manager works without its background daemon).
+     * Treat any service start/open failure here as best-effort success. */
+    if (r != ERROR_SUCCESS)
+    {
+        WARN( "vstpoc: ignoring StartServices failure for service %s — continuing install\n",
+             debugstr_w(name) );
+        r = ERROR_SUCCESS;
+    }
+
     uirow = MSI_CreateRecord( 2 );
     MSI_RecordSetStringW( uirow, 1, display_name );
     MSI_RecordSetStringW( uirow, 2, name );
